<div id="review_4233601740" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4233601740" />
    <a title="Grady" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1362506-grady"><img alt="Grady" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442472304p2/1362506.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4233601740?book_show_action=true">Sep 12, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Grady" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Grady" href="/user/show/1362506-grady">Grady</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4233601740" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10728665802933823807">A fountain of wisdom – and hope!<br/><br/>California author/educator/futurist Newton Lee is the founder of Disney Online Technology, creator of AT&amp;T Bell Labs original AI tool, and among many other accomplishments he is the chairman of the California Transhumanist Party, Education and Media advisor to the US Transhumanist Party, and president of the Institute for Education, Research and Scholarships! This book is a compilation of essays by many experts in all fields, deftly edited by Newton Lee in an engr</span>
  <span id="freeText10728665802933823807" style="display:none">A fountain of wisdom – and hope!<br /><br />California author/educator/futurist Newton Lee is the founder of Disney Online Technology, creator of AT&amp;T Bell Labs original AI tool, and among many other accomplishments he is the chairman of the California Transhumanist Party, Education and Media advisor to the US Transhumanist Party, and president of the Institute for Education, Research and Scholarships! This book is a compilation of essays by many experts in all fields, deftly edited by Newton Lee in an engrossing and involving manner.<br /><br />Lee opens this hefty volume by stating, ‘Modern humanity with some 5,000 years of recorded history has been experiencing growing pains, with no end in sight. It is high time for humanity to grow up and to transcend itself by embracing transhumanism. Jesus said to his disciples in the Garden of Gethsemane, ”the spirit is willing, but the flesh is weak.” (Matthew 26:410. The current capability of human cognition wakes the interpretation of God a difficult matter even for the genius Albert Einstein who wrote in a 1954 letter, “The word god is for me nothing more than the expression and product of human weaknesses.” To err is human, whether we are religious, atheist, or agnostic…’<br /><br />For many, the term Transhumanism needs definition: a ‘social and philosophical movement devoted to promoting the development of robust human-enhancement technologies that would augment or increase human sensory reception, emotive ability, or cognitive capacity as well as radically improve human health and extended life spans. Such modifications resulting form the addition of biological or physical technologies would be more or less permanent and integrated into the human body.’ <br /><br />Through an extensive plethora of impressive essays from experts, Lee includes topics of the history of transhumanism, The boundaries of the human: From Humanism to Transhumanism, The US Transhumanism Party and the politics of abundance, Artificial and Superintelligence, Creating conversational AI capable of uncommon range and empathy for the betterment of business and humanity, Humanizing machines, Ethics and bias in machine learning, Philosophical Moral and Ethical rationalization of AI, Transhumanism and the older adult quality of life, Future of Regenerative medicine, and on and on. This is a massive publication and should be read and digested in small amounts at a time for complete understanding and acceptance of a future that is very possibly bright.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10728665802933823807" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


