<div id="review_4259605686" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4259605686" />
    <a title="Grymm Gevierre" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/110261611-grymm-gevierre"><img alt="Grymm Gevierre" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1616326387p2/110261611.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4259605686?book_show_action=true">Sep 27, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Grymm Gevierre" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Grymm Gevierre" href="/user/show/110261611-grymm-gevierre">Grymm Gevierre</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4259605686" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14685054611917023612">This book is a massive and exciting undertaking. Newton Lee is the credited editor of the book, but many contributors are credited in this tome, along with several sources cited. With so many contributors, you’d think the voice would be scattered, but Lee does a great job pulling it all together. <br/><br/>The concept of this book is expanding beyond the traditional human experience and quite literally transcending the division between us. This book is not a casual read but a great study. It quite literal</span>
  <span id="freeText14685054611917023612" style="display:none">This book is a massive and exciting undertaking. Newton Lee is the credited editor of the book, but many contributors are credited in this tome, along with several sources cited. With so many contributors, you’d think the voice would be scattered, but Lee does a great job pulling it all together. <br /><br />The concept of this book is expanding beyond the traditional human experience and quite literally transcending the division between us. This book is not a casual read but a great study. It quite literally is a handbook and a reference piece. It’s very educational on the human condition and social sciences from a perspective that homes in on many things that we hope to see in societal progression and humankind’s evolution into the next giant leap forward. <br /><br />If transhumanism is even of remote interest to you, then you need this book on your shelf.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14685054611917023612" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
